    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="731"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">864.4016/8–244: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-02">August 2,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received August 11—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–455. American Interests—Hungary. Department’s airgram 252 May 26.<note n="26"
                        xml:id="d731fn26">Not printed; it inquired concerning a decree affecting
                        Jews in Hungary (864.4016/187).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Swiss Foreign Office note July 31 states decree mentioned Legation’s 2505 April
                        20th<note n="27" xml:id="d731fn27">Telegram not printed.</note> appeared
                    Hungarian Official Gazette April 16th and paragraph 14 reads in translation as
                    follows.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The provisions of the present decree are not applicable to those foreign
                        citizens residing in Hungary who upon request of the competent foreign
                        representative authorities prove their foreign citizenship by a certificate
                        issued for that purpose by the Foreign Control Bureau providing however that
                        reciprocity exists in that respect with the state of which the Jew is a
                        citizen.”</p>
                </quote>
                <pb facs="1214" n="1200" xml:id="pg_1200"/>
                <p>Swiss Legation Budapest reported that since publication decree it has taken steps
                    that Americans under its protection benefit paragraph 14 and is of the opinion
                    that property Americans in Hungary not affected by government measures.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
